                <p>
                    <milestone n="A" unit="zone" type="pagelike"/>
                    <label>Northern façade, westernmost wall section</label>
                    <lb n="1"/>|||<hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi> || <hi rend="grantha">kuvalāla</hi>-<hi rend="grantha">samudbhavaḥ</hi> <hi rend="grantha">su</hi>-<hi rend="grantha">kī</hi><unclear><hi rend="grantha">r</hi></unclear><hi rend="grantha">tti</hi>-
                    <lb n="2"/><hi rend="grantha">pa</hi>ḻuvūr-<hi rend="grantha">na</hi><unclear>k</unclear>ka <hi rend="grantha">Iti</hi> <hi rend="grantha">pratīta</hi>-<hi rend="grantha">nāmā</hi> <hi rend="grantha">muravairīva</hi> <unclear><hi rend="grantha">vira</hi></unclear>
                    <lb n="3"/><hi rend="grantha">jaḥ</hi><note>Swaminathan (SII 32) reads <unclear>khya</unclear>ḥ.</note> <hi rend="grantha">jāta</hi>-<hi rend="grantha">varṇṇa</hi>-<unclear><hi rend="grantha">pra</hi></unclear><hi rend="grantha">varo</hi> <hi rend="grantha">va</hi><note>SII reads<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi> but clearly it is not.</note><hi rend="grantha">ṃśa</hi>-<hi rend="grantha">karaḥ</hi> <hi rend="grantha">sam</hi>-<hi rend="grantha">āvirāsīt</hi> <unclear>||</unclear>
                    <lb n="4"/><hi rend="grantha">yam artthinas tyāga</hi><note>SII reads<hi rend="grantha">ya</hi>.</note><hi rend="grantha">m upātta-v</hi><unclear><hi rend="grantha">i</hi></unclear><hi rend="grantha">graham dvi</hi><note>SII reads<hi rend="grantha">bi</hi>.</note><hi rend="grantha">ṣat-janāḥ </hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>śau</unclear></hi>
                    <lb n="5"/><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>r</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">yya-guṇaṃ śarīriṇam Anaṃgam aṃgānvayinam mṛgekṣa</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>ṇā</unclear></hi>
                    <lb n="6"/><hi rend="grantha">vida</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>n</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">ti dhar</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>m</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">maṃ satan</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>u</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">m vipaścitaḥ</hi> ||| – <hi rend="grantha">soyaṃ sva-vikramā</hi><unclear><hi rend="grantha">pta</hi></unclear>-
                    <lb n="7"/><hi rend="grantha">khilārṇṇavāṃbarākara-grahād vīryya-toṣitād v</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>i</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">krama-coḷa-nṛpāl la-</hi>
                    <lb n="8"/><hi rend="grantha">bdha-vikrama-coḷa-mahārājābhidho ‘sya rājñaś catu</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>r</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">daśe varṣe maha-</hi>
                    <lb n="9"/><hi rend="grantha">ti śrī-vānavan-mahādevy-agrahare śrī-vijayamaṃgale vasataḥ śa-</hi>
                    <lb n="10"/><hi rend="grantha">mbhoḥ mandiraṃ śilā-mayam vidhāyāsyaiva grāmasya svabh</hi><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>ū</unclear></hi><hi rend="grantha">tāṃ ne-</hi>
                    <lb n="11"/><hi rend="grantha">ṭuvāyil-nāma-grāmaṭikām mahāparṣadaḥ krītvā sva-vitta-dānād aka-</hi>
                    <lb n="12"/><hi rend="grantha">rāñ ca kṛtvā tasyaiva śaṃbhor ā-śaśāṃka-sthiter arccanotsavādy-arttha-</hi>
                    <lb n="13"/><hi rend="grantha">m prādāt</hi> || – kopparake<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi>ripa<hi rend="grantha">nma</hi>kku yāṇṭu 14 Āvatu Uṭaiy
                    <lb n="14"/>ār peru<unclear>ṉ</unclear>tiṟattu kuvalālam uṭaiyāṉ Ampalavan paḻuvūr
                    <lb n="15"/>nakkaṉāṉa vi<hi rend="grantha">krama</hi>coḻa <hi rend="grantha">mahārāja</hi>neṉ vaṭa ka<unclear>r</unclear>ai <hi rend="grantha">brahmade</hi>ya
                    <lb n="16"/>m periya <hi rend="grantha"><unclear>śrī</unclear></hi> vanavaṉ <hi rend="grantha">mahāde</hi>vi<unclear>catu<hi rend="grantha">vvedi</hi></unclear>maṅ<unclear>ka</unclear>lattu <hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi> vi<hi rend="grantha">ja</hi>yamaṅkala<unclear>t</unclear>
                    <lb n="17"/>tu<hi rend="grantha">mahāde</hi>var <hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi> vimāṉam kallāl Eḻuṉtaruḷuvittu I<hi rend="grantha">de</hi>vark<unclear>ku</unclear>t ti
                    <lb n="18"/>ruvamitukkum tiruviḷakkukkum<hi rend="grantha">śrī bali</hi>kkum tirumeypūccukkum tiruppūkaik
                    <lb n="19"/>kum tirunaṉtavānappuṟattukkum tiruviḻāvukkum<hi rend="grantha">snapa</hi>ṉaṅkaḷukkum maṟṟum
                    <lb n="20"/>I<hi rend="grantha">de</hi>varkku veṇṭum Ārātiṉaikaḷ Eppeṟpaṭṭaṉa Avaiccukkum Uttama <unclear>I</unclear> <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> <note><p>This<hi rend="grantha">uttama X X</hi> (SII reads <hi rend="grantha">gram</hi> after uttama but I am not sure it is right) is written in smaller letters and may be connected to the following few lines engraved on the pilaster:</p><p>yo<hi rend="grantha">gi</hi> kalamupatu</p><p>˚iccivayo<hi rend="grantha">gi</hi></p><p><hi rend="grantha">brāhma</hi>ṇāvo X</p><p>vallor<unclear>i</unclear> ˚a<unclear>puvi</unclear></p><p>{unlegible}</p></note> 
                    <lb n="21"/><note>There are a few words added on the pilaster before the line: ˚aka X na // X X X</note> mākaṉāṉ kuṭutta Ū<unclear>r</unclear>āva<unclear>tu</unclear> Ip-periya <hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi>-vānavaṉ-<hi rend="grantha">mahā-de</hi>vi<hi rend="grantha">ca</hi>tu<hi rend="grantha">rvvedi</hi>ma
                    
                    <label>Western façade, northernmost wall section</label>
                    <lb n="22"/><note>First line of the northernmost wall section of the western façade.</note> ṅkalattu vaṭapiṭākai neṭuvāyilum
                    <lb n="23"/>Itu <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> ppaṭu<note>SII reads<hi rend="grantha">ca</hi> instead of <hi rend="grantha">ṭu</hi>.</note>m Ūrtāmaraiṉal
                    <lb n="24"/>Ārum tiruccen<unclear>i</unclear>valamum ma<unclear>ṇ</unclear>kulakku
                    <lb n="25"/>ṟucciyum Uḷppaṭa Ineṭuvāyil vaḷai
                    <lb n="26"/>yilc cuṟṟumuṟṟum Ivūr ni <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> <unclear>i</unclear> la <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> m paṉ
                    <lb n="27"/>ceyūm meṉceyum menokk[[i]]na maramum [[ki]]<unclear>ḻ</unclear>
                    <lb n="28"/>ṉokkina kiṇaṟum kuḷamum koṭṭakamum paṟṟum teṟṟiyu <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> 
                    <lb n="29"/>ṟṟum Uṭumpoṭi Āmaitavaḻṇtatu Eppeṟppaṭa
                    <lb n="30"/>tum Ivūr Ilaikkalam<unclear>u</unclear>m ta<unclear>ṟi</unclear>ppuṭavaiyum kaṇ
                    <lb n="31"/>ṇālak [[kā]]ṇamum [[i]]<unclear>kāṟ</unclear>ppāṭṭamum Ulaiyam Ulaippāṭṭamum
                    <lb n="32"/>Uḷppa Ivū<unclear>r</unclear> vaḷaiyilc cuṟṟumuṟṟum I<unclear>p</unclear>periya<hi rend="grantha">śrī </hi>vānavaṉ
                    <lb n="33"/><hi rend="grantha">mahāde</hi>[[vi]]<unclear><hi rend="grantha">cca</hi></unclear>tu<hi rend="grantha">vve</hi>timaṅkalattu peruṅkuṟip peru<hi rend="grantha">ma</hi>kkaḷ [[pa]]kkal vilai
                    <lb n="34"/>koṇṭu Uṭaiyeṉṉā Im<hi rend="grantha">mahāsabhai</hi>yārkke Eḻu<unclear>ṉūṟu</unclear> kācu ku<unclear>ṭu</unclear>
                    <lb n="35"/>tta Iṟai Iḻicca Ipparicu Iṟai Iliyāka ṉān Uṭai En<unclear>ṉā</unclear>y Iru<unclear>ṉ</unclear>
                    <lb n="36"/><note>There is a space between the lines 35 and 36. And the writing changes slightly. Is it the same inscription?</note> ta Ineṭuvāyil muṟṟum I <hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi> v<unclear>i</unclear><hi rend="grantha">ja</hi>yamaṅkalattu <hi rend="grantha">mahāde</hi>varkku mu
                    <lb n="37"/>ṉ cuṭṭappaṭṭa Eppeṟppaṭṭa taruvārātiṉaikaḷukkum<hi rend="grantha">bhogamā</hi>kak kuṭutte
                    <lb n="38"/>ṉ kuvalāḷamuṭaiyān Ampalavaṉ paḻuvūr nakkaṉāṉa vi<hi rend="grantha">kramaśo</hi>ḻa <hi rend="grantha">mahā</hi>
                    <lb n="39"/><hi rend="grantha">rāj</hi><unclear>ā</unclear>naṉ Ivai pan<hi rend="grantha">mahā</hi> E[[śva]]ra ra<hi rend="grantha">kṣai</hi> Aṟamm aṟavekka Aṟamm allatu tuṇaiyilai
                    <lb n="40"/>I<unclear>va</unclear> colla Eḻutinne Ivūr<hi rend="grantha">maddhastha</hi>n ninṟān Ārā Amutān vānavamātevip peruṅk<unclear>ā</unclear>
                    <lb n="41"/>vitiy Ivai Enneḻuttu
                </p>
                
